The course is a follow-up to "Russian for Beginners". The aim of the course is to establish associations so that the students would be able to independently work with ESP literature, and would cope with simple conversation situations. Assessment: Pass/fail examinationObjectives/eesmärkid:  Obtaining knowledge of Russian language phonetics, grammar and syntax main rules that will facilitate fluent communication on the common level and generic texts understanding and analytical usage. Using of minimum glossary that will allow to work with legal texts.. The course revises and reinforces the skills acquired at the basic level, develops the skills in expressing oneself in oral and in writtenLearning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After the course, the students can:
* can understand the essential in a familiar topic (studies, working, free time etc.);
* can compile texts on a familiar topic or a topic interesting for the student both in the oral and written mode, and use the newly acquired grammatical structures in the right way;
* can describe experiences and plans, exchange important information and express their opinion on practical problems;
- can find necessary information from everyday texts (advertisements, menus, schedules) and can understand the gist of radio and TV programmes that are broadcast slowly and clearly, if these include familiar or interesting topics;
* can participate in short conversations on everyday matters and in ordinary situations without prior preparation;
* can make social contact (greeting, saying good-bye, introduction, thanking, agreeing on a time to meet, etc.)*- can write short simple coherent texts)
